on branches exist when the degree of anisotropy of material $A$ is\ngreater. If $\\chi = 0^\\circ$ then a solitary DTV solution exists for a unique\npropagation direction on each DT branch solution. If $\\chi > 0^\\circ$, then no\nDTV solutions exist. As the degree of nonhomogeneity of material $B$ decreases,\nthe number of DT solution branches decreases.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 5 Feb 2020 15:24:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-05-20"}
